org.gbif.registry.metadata.parse

Class DatasetWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.registry.metadata.parse.DatasetWrapper

  • public class DatasetWrapper
extends Object
    A delegating wrapper to a Dataset that can be instructed to override existing content or not. This allows an existing Dataset to be augmented by new content.

      • addCuratorial

        public void addCuratorial(org.gbif.api.model.registry.eml.curatorial.CuratorialUnitComposite curatorialUnit)
        We only ever expect a single set of curatorial units per Collection. The Curatorial Units are outside the Collection element in the GBIF EML schema, so it's by strong assumption that the units belong to the collection.

      • setPubDateAsString

        public void setPubDateAsString(String pubDateAsString)
        Sets the publication date, converting from input String to Date. The beanutils DateTime can't be converted, because this property isn't registered as a proper bean, it is parsed out by the addMethod as a String.
        Parameters:
        pubDateAsString - publication date as String

      • setSpecimenPreservationMethod

        public void setSpecimenPreservationMethod(org.gbif.api.vocabulary.PreservationMethodType type)
        The property should be set against Collection and allow for multiple Collection. There were difficulties doing this because the element is outside the element so the two properties need to be joined via separate parsing blocks. This is a bit of a hack, assuming there is only ever a single Collection object, and that there is only ever a single SpecimenPreservationMethod that belongs to it. Sets the SpecimenPreservationMethodType on Collection.
        Parameters:
        type - PreservationMethodType
